Package: industtry
Type: Package
Title: A toolkit for structured datasets exploitation
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Daniel Rakotomalala
Maintainer: Daniel Rakotomalala <rakdanielh@gmail.com>
Description: A set of functions that helps exploiting structured datasets 
    (data frames) with an industrialization approach. 
    Industrialization here means applying as efficiently as possible the same
    procedure to any number of inputs as long as these inputs have a common structure. 
License: Public domain license
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
URL: https://github.com/danielrak/industtry
BugReports: https://github.com/danielrak/industtry/issues
Imports: 
    dplyr (>= 1.1.3),
    lubridate (>= 1.9.2),
    magrittr (>= 2.0.3),
    plyr (>= 1.8.8),
    purrr (>= 1.0.2),
    rio (>= 1.0.1),
    stringr (>= 1.5.0),
    tibble (>= 3.2.1),
    tools (>= 4.3.1),
    writexl (>= 1.4.2)
